OwO Shop: Wallpapers
Purchase a wallpaper for your profile!
- **`owo shop wp {page}`** to view the wallpaper as images
- **`owo buy {id}`** to buy an item
- **`owo wallpaper`** to view your wallpapers
- **`owo profile set wallpaper {id}`** to use it

OwO Shop: Rings
Purchase a ring to propose to someone!
All rings are the same. Different tiers are available to show off your love!
- **`owo buy {id}`** to buy an item
- **`owo sell {id}`** to sell an item for 75% of its original price
- **`owo marry @user {id}`** to use the ring

09Miles's team
`owo team add {animal} {pos}` Add an animal to your team
`owo team remove {pos}` Removes an animal from your team
`owo team rename {name}` Renames your team

Weapons are randomly generated every day!

- **`owo shop weapon`** to view the weapons

OwO Shop: Rings
Purchase a ring to propose to someone!
All rings are the same. Different tiers are available to show off your love!
- **`owo buy {id}`** to buy an item
- **`owo sell {id}`** to sell an item for 75% of its original price
- **`owo marry @user {id}`** to use the ring

OwO Shop: Rings
Purchase a ring to propose to someone!
All rings are the same. Different tiers are available to show off your love!
- **`owo buy {id}`** to buy an item
- **`owo sell {id}`** to sell an item for 75% of its original price
- **`owo marry @user {id}`** to use the ring

`owo setteam {teamNum}` to set multiple teams

üõ†Ô∏è __**Server Settings**__ üõ†Ô∏è
(Server not premium)

¬∑ Prefix: **$** ($prefix)
¬∑ Lang: **en** ($lang)
¬∑ Claim reset: every **180** min. ($setclaim)
¬∑ Exact minute of the reset: xx:**20** ($setinterval)
¬∑ Reset shifted: by +**0** min. ($shifthour)
¬∑ Rolls per hour: **10** ($setrolls)
¬∑ Time before the claim reaction expires: **30** sec. ($settimer)
¬∑ Spawn rarity multiplicator for already claimed characters: **2** ($setrare)
¬∑ Server game mode: **1** ($gamemode)
¬∑ This channel instance: **1** ($channelinstance)
¬∑ Slash commands: enabled ($toggleslash)

¬∑ Ranking: enabled ($toggleclaimrank/$togglelikerank)
¬∑ Ranks displayed during rolls: **disabled** ($togglerolls)
¬∑ Hentai series: enabled ($togglehentai)
¬∑ Disturbing imagery series: enabled ($toggledisturbing)
¬∑ Rolls sniping: 0 ($togglesnipe)
¬∑ Kakera sniping: 0 ($togglekakerasnipe)
¬∑ Limit of characters per harem: **8100** ($haremlimit)
¬∑ Reacts: ****for public wishes only**** ($togglereact)
¬∑ Custom reactions: no ($claimreact)

¬∑ Kakera trading: enabled ($togglekakeratrade)
¬∑ Kakera calculation: claims and likes ranks (and number of claimed characters) ($togglekakeraclaim/$togglekakeralike)
¬∑ Kakera value displayed during rolls: **disabled** ($togglekakerarolls)
¬∑ $kakeraloot wishprotect: enabled ($togglewishprotect)

[25-Sep-22 04:11 PM] Mudae#0807


{Embed}
1/17 - Tutorial
This tutorial will guide you through the main features of Mudae.
To change the language (fr, pt-br or es), type **$lang** (admin command).
if you have already done this tutorial on another server, you can skip and get the rewards with **$skiptuto**


:did: **COLLECT YOUR FIRST CHARACTER**
Type $w to spawn a random waifu or $h for a random husbando. This is called a roll.
To collect (claim) a character, quickly add a reaction to the roll.
By default you have 30 seconds to react and you can claim one character every 3 hours.
You can add the letter g ($wg, $hg) to only spawn video game characters, or the letter a ($wa, $ha) to not spawn video game specific characters.
Use $m (or $ma, $mg) if you don't have a gender preference.


:do: **CHECK YOUR COLLECTED CHARACTERS**
Type $mm to see your list of claimed characters.
A character can only be owned by one person in each server.
This list is not global: it is bound to this server only.


**Reward: 200:kakera:**

{Embed}
Spend your:kakera:to build the 12 floors of the tower:
- Choose a different perk each time you build a floor
- The next floor is more expensive (+5000 per floor, $towervalue)
- You can restart your tower and be refunded with $destroy
- The construction might be infinite: if you manage to build the 12 floors, you can build an additional tower with lower bonuses (the cost keeps increasing)


Your current level is **0** 
The next level costs **5000**:kakera:
You have **0**:kakera:

Build a floor by using **$build <perk number>**

List of perks and their corresponding numbers:

**1** = +2 wishlist slots
**2** = Increased spawn chance for your $firstwish: **+**50%
**3** = +1 disablelist slot and +1627.8 disablelist size
**4** = 30% chance to earn a 2nd key when you get a bronze key on your wishes
**5** = 20% chance to earn a 2nd key when you get a silver key on your wishes
**6** = 10% chance to earn a 2nd key when you get a gold key on your wishes
**7** = Max kakera power increased to 110%
**8** = Kakera reactions cost -4% kakera power
**9** = Gold keys max bonus increased by +500 kakera/3h
**10** = Light kakera give +1 random kakera
**11** = +1 roll per hour
**12** = $colormm and $colorpr commands unlocked

4, 5 & 6 also give +1% chance for chaos keys and don't work for wished series

[29-Sep-22 09:45 AM] Mudae#0807
**info slash**: Slash commands are commands that start with the prefix **/**
Type **/** to see the list of available commands. They have the same effects as their $-prefix counterparts.
This is a recent and enforced Discord feature with advantages and inconvenients. You can only send 2 slash commands every 5 seconds.

When you roll with a slash command, the roll has a bonus of **+10%** wish spawn and **+10%** kakera earned (bronze/emerald and reacts) and the time to react is doubled (if no one flooded too much between your rolls).

Syntax example for flags ($s flags) and other subcommands (such as $notepage):
Type **/mm /wr Re:Zero** instead of $mmwr Re:Zero

If you have issues with slash commands:
- If you are on mobile, update your Discord.
- Your role (not the bot's role) must have the channel permissions to **Use slash commands**.
- Check if slash commands are enabled in your Discord settings -> Text & Images.
- Kick and reinvite the bot with the link provided by **$invite** (nothing is lost).
- Give the permission "**Use External Emojis**" to the role **everyone**
**$toggleslash**: (MOD) Disable the slash commands for your server and all its instances.


[29-Sep-22 09:45 AM] Tabmow#0054

[29-Sep-22 09:46 AM] Mudae#0807
Syntax: $addcustom **name**$**gender**$**type of rolls**$**imgur link**
This will add a custom character for your server (1000 max, can be rolled and given)

Replace **gender** with `f` for female, `m` for male or `fm` for both/genderless
Replace **type of rolls** with `animanga`, `game` or `both`

Commands for an already existing custom character:
- For an image addition/change: `$acimg` (or $ic)
- For a name addition/change: `$acname` (or $nc)
- For a gender or roulette change: `$acgender` or `$actype`
You can also delete the character with `$deletecustom`

[30-Sep-22 04:21 PM] Mudae#0807
Syntax: **$im** <character to search>

**$im** <character>$<page> to jump to the page.
**$imq!** <character> if you want to return the list instead of one character.
**$ime** to display the character tags.
**$ims** for a direct message of the images.
**$imo** to display the user Discord ID.
**$imd** for more details during inexact searches.
**$imq+** <character> (or $imq- <character>) to only search for names containing a part starting (or ending) exactly by your request.

Characters disabled from your rolls ($disable, $togglewestern...) are indicated with üö´

2/17 - Tutorial
:do: **SEARCH A SERIES IN THE DATABASE**
Type $ima <series> to search any series in the database.
Never add the "<" and ">", it just means the word between those symbols has to be replaced.
For example, type $ima attack on titan


:do: **SEARCH A CHARACTER IN THE DATABASE**
Type $im <character> to search any character in the database. For example, type $im asuna


:do: **WISH A CHARACTER**
Type $wish <character> to wish a character. When a wished character spawns, you are mentioned in the channel.
Later, you can also boost the spawn probability of your wished characters with kakera (ingame currency)


**Reward: 1 $freeclaim**

2/17 - Tutorial
:did: **SEARCH A SERIES IN THE DATABASE**
Type $ima <series> to search any series in the database.
Never add the "<" and ">", it just means the word between those symbols has to be replaced.
For example, type $ima attack on titan


:did: **SEARCH A CHARACTER IN THE DATABASE**
Type $im <character> to search any character in the database. For example, type $im asuna


:do: **WISH A CHARACTER**
Type $wish <character> to wish a character. When a wished character spawns, you are mentioned in the channel.
Later, you can also boost the spawn probability of your wished characters with kakera (ingame currency)


**Reward: 1 $freeclaim**

3/17 - Tutorial
:do: **CHECK WHEN YOUR NEXT CLAIM RESET IS**

[01-Oct-22 09:18 PM] 09Miles#8861
$togglesniipe


[01-Oct-22 09:18 PM] 09Miles#8861
$togglesnipe


[01-Oct-22 09:18 PM] Mudae#0807
Use one of the syntaxes below to change the way people can snipe characters on your server (= if players are able to claim the characters rolled by other players or not). Wishseries aren't considered as wishes for this command.

**$togglesnipe 0**: (default value, no restriction) Any character rolled can be sniped by anyone.

**$togglesnipe 1**: (partial restriction) When someone rolls a character they have in their character wishlist, this character can't be sniped for 8 seconds.

**$togglesnipe 2**: (full restriction) Any character rolled can't be sniped for 8 seconds.

**$togglesnipe 3**: (wish restriction 1) When someone rolls a WISHED character, this character can't be sniped for 8 seconds EXCEPT for people wishing for this character (AND the roller)

**$togglesnipe 4**: (wish restriction 2) When someone rolls a WISHED character, this character can't be sniped for 8 seconds EXCEPT for people wishing for this character (the roller CAN'T claim this character either, except if they wished for it)

**$togglesnipe 5**: (combined restriction 1) Any character rolled can't be sniped for 8 second(s) EXCEPT for people wishing for this character (AND the roller)

**$togglesnipe 6**: (combined restriction 2) Any character rolled can't be sniped for 8 second(s) EXCEPT for people wishing for this character (the roller CAN'T claim this wish except if they wished for it)

You can add an option to modify the 8 seconds default value.
Example: **$togglesnipe 1 2.5**
=> Anyone will be able to react after 2.5 seconds.

Current value: **0**


[01-Oct-22 09:18 PM] 09Miles#8861
$togglesnipe 2


[01-Oct-22 09:18 PM] Mudae#0807
Command restricted to admins (Discord permissions: administrator). Use $restrict to allow specific roles.

{Embed}
3/17 - Tutorial
:did: **CHECK WHEN YOUR NEXT CLAIM RESET IS**
Type $mu to see when you can claim a character again. For the next rolls reset, it's $ru


:did: **HAVE VOTED AT LEAST ONE TIME FOR THE BOT AND TYPE $VOTE**
Type $vote to get the link. You get a rolls reset each time you vote, stocked indefinitely until you type $rolls


:did: **RESET YOUR ROLLS WITH $ROLLS**
When all your rolls are used, you can reset them with $rolls


:do: **COLLECT A SECOND CHARACTER**
You can either wait for your next claim reset, or consume the freeclaim you got (type $fc to use it)


**Reward: 200:kakera:**

**Reward: +2 $preset for wishlist**


[02-Oct-22 08:33 AM] 09Miles#8861
$wish


[02-Oct-22 08:33 AM] Mudae#0807
Syntax: **$wish** <character>
Effect: you will be mentioned when the character spawns.
The spawnrate of wishes is the same as any character but they can be boosted with kakera (see $k and $kt).
For multiple characters, separate them with a $

**$wishlist**: your list of wishes. Or $wlt (details) and most of the flags (see $s flags)
**$wishremove** <character>: remove a character from your wishlist (or **$wishremoveall**)
**$wishdm**: change the ping options.
**$wishsort**: automatically sort your wishlist by alphabetical order.
**$wishpurge**: remove doubles and already claimed characters (or **$wpx** to purge while keeping wishes for characters claimed by yourself)

Use **$wishd** instead of $wish to instantly delete your message
Use **$wishl** instead of $wish to lock your wish (effects: not affected by $wp and $wpx)
Use **$wishk** instead of $wish to wish for more kakera (effects: __+220__ kakera instead of +200 with Silver IV bonus, __mentions/DM disabled__ when the character spawns and not considered as a wish for the wishprotect kakeraloot feature)
You can combine those options. Example: $wishdlk

**Note:** characters in your wishlist and wishserieslist are NOT disabled by your $disablelist!

4/17 - Tutorial

This is how you get more help and subcommands about a command.

[02-Oct-22 08:33 AM] 09Miles#8861
$search wish


[02-Oct-22 08:33 AM] Mudae#0807
**$wish**: Wish for characters. *$wish Rem*
**$wishremove**: ($wr) Remove a wish from your $wishlist.
**$wishlist**: ($wl) Your list of wished characters. See `$wish` and `$s flags`
**$wishremoveall**: ($wrall) Remove all the wishes from your $wishlist
**$wishd**: ($wd) Wish for characters while deleting this wish message.
**$wishk**: ($wk) Same as $wish but you get more kakera with Silver IV and no mentions.
**$wishl**: Wish for characters who won't be removed by $wishpurge
**$boostwish**: ($bw) Invest bonus rolls to boost the spawn of your wishes and your $firstwish
**$wishdm**: Make your wishes private and/or get a DM when they spawn.
**$wishsort**: Always sort your wishlist by alphabetical order.
**$wishpurge**: ($wp) Remove already claimed characters (and duplicates) from your wishlist.
**$firstwish**: ($fw) Define a favorite wish. Its spawn can be boosted with $kt and $tuto rewards.
**$wishseries**: (PLAYER PREMIUM, $ws) Wish for a series (not affected by bonuses such as kakera)
**$wishserieslist**: (PLAYER PREMIUM, $wsl) Your list of wished series. See `$wishseries`
**$clearwishes**: (MOD) Remove all the wishes for someone.
**$qs**: Save your current wishlist, disablelist or antidisablelist. *$qs wl*
**$ql**: Load your saved wishlist, disablelist or antidisablelist. *$ql wl*
**$qw**: Display your saved wishlist #1. For the #2, use $qw2

{Embed}
5/17 - Tutorial
:do: **CHECK YOUR KAKERA**
Type $kakera
This is the main command for infos and progression related to the kakera system.
With kakera you can unlock a lot of different bonuses.


:do: **GET KAKERA WITH $DK**
This is a quick method to get more kakera.


:do: **SUCCESSFULLY REACT TO A KAKERA**
Kakera reactions appear under the rolls of some already claimed characters.
The more your server has claimed characters, the less kakera reactions will appear under already claimed characters.


:do: **SEE YOUR LIST OF COMMANDS COOLDOWNS**
Type $tu to retrieve your $mu, $ru and more cooldowns.


:do: **USE YOUR FIRST FLAG: $MMK**
For some commands you can add any letter to change what is displayed.
Here, you add the letter "k" to the command "$mm" in order to display the kakera values.


**Reward: 200:kakera:**


[02-Oct-22 08:34 AM] 09Miles#8861
%kakera


[02-Oct-22 08:34 AM] 09Miles#8861
$kakera


[02-Oct-22 08:34 AM] Mudae#0807


{Embed}
How to collect kakera in your server (change the options with $togglekakera):
- $dailykakera
- React on the:kakera:that could appear on ** some already claimed** rolls ($setrare)
- Divorce a character with **$divorce** (value depends on claim/like ranks AND number of claimed characters)
- Trade with other players ($me with `<number> ka` or $givekakera)

You have **598**:kakera:!

Melt your kakera into power badges:
**Bronze 0** ¬∑ Next level: **1000**:kakera: +1 wishlist slot
**Silver 0** ¬∑ Next level: **2000**:kakera: +25% wishlist spawn
**Gold 0** ¬∑ Next level: **3000**:kakera: -10% kakera power usage ($ku)
??? ¬∑ Prerequisites: Bronze I + Silver I + Gold I or 2 badges IV
??? ¬∑ Prerequisites: Bronze II + Silver II + Gold II or 2 badges IV
??? ¬∑ Prerequisites: Bronze III + Silver III + Gold III or 2 badges IV

**Kakeratower:** $kt
**Kakeraloots:** $infokl



Unlock a level with **$bronze**, **$silver**...
Get a special kakera **bonus** when you reach a level max (IV)!

Spend a total of **8000**:kakera:to enhance multitrading
Each level also gives you the corresponding **badge** on your $profile

5/17 - Tutorial
:did: **CHECK YOUR KAKERA**
Type $kakera
This is the main command for infos and progression related to the kakera system.
With kakera you can unlock a lot of different bonuses.


:did: **GET KAKERA WITH $DK**
This is a quick method to get more kakera.


:do: **SUCCESSFULLY REACT TO A KAKERA**
Kakera reactions appear under the rolls of some already claimed characters.
The more your server has claimed characters, the less kakera reactions will appear under already claimed characters.


:do: **SEE YOUR LIST OF COMMANDS COOLDOWNS**
Type $tu to retrieve your $mu, $ru and more cooldowns.


:do: **USE YOUR FIRST FLAG: $MMK**
For some commands you can add any letter to change what is displayed.
Here, you add the letter "k" to the command "$mm" in order to display the kakera values.


**Reward: 200:kakera:**

$mmk

{Embed}
6/17 - Tutorial
:do: **USE THE SEARCH COMMAND TO GET MORE INFOS ABOUT FLAGS**
With $search flags
Flags are numerous and can be combined at will...


:do: **USE ANOTHER FLAG: $MMI**
"i" is a flag to display the images.


:do: **COMBINE TWO FLAGS: $MMIS**
Which means "$mm" + "i" flag + "s" flag.
"s" flag is used to send the command by DM.


:do: **DIRECTLY JUMP TO A SPECIFIC $IM PAGE**
Use $im <character> $ <number> to directly jump to the image number.
The "$" is called a separator (it separates the character name and the page number)
This works for numerous commands, such as $mm <page>


:do: **CHANGE THE IMAGE OF A CHARACTER YOU OWN**
When you type $im <character> and change the pages, the image position is indicated at the bottom.
Use $changeimg <character> $ <image position> to display that image by default.


**Reward: 200:kakera:**


[05-Oct-22 06:33 PM] 09Miles#8861
$search flags


[05-Oct-22 06:33 PM] Mudae#0807
**info flags**: Add those letters to some commands ($mm, $ima...) to display different informations:
**w** (waifu), **h** (husbando), **wh** (both genders), **w=** (waifu without both genders), **h=** (husbando without both genders)
**g** (game), **g-** (animanga), **gg-** (both), **g=** (game only), **g-=** (animanga only)
**a** (series list), **a+** (series names), **b** (series bundles), **p** (character search if you type some text), **s** (DM)

**r** (claim ranks), **r-** (claim ranks not sorted), **l** (like ranks), **l-** (like ranks not sorted),
**k** (kakera value), **k=** (kakera sorted), **k-** (kakera base value)
**y** (keys only), **y=** (keys sorted), **y+** (with full harem), **y-** (without keys)
Equivalent for soulkeys: **y!**, **y!=**, **y!+**, **y!-**
**c** (embedcolored), **c+** (with full harem), **c-** (without embedcolor)

**t** (type of rolls), **m** (main names), **d** (img/alias details), **v** (hide details such as notes), **n** (not noted), **n+** (noted only)
**u** (unclaimed), **o** (owner names), **o=** (owned only), **o-** (not owned by you), **o+** (owned by you)
**o!** (flags are about you when checking another user)
**x** (disabled), **x+** (with full harem), **x-** (not disabled)
**q!** (inexact search), **q=** (exact search), **q+** (exact start), **q-** (exact end), **==** (alphabetical sort)
**i** (images), **i-** (hide images if DM)

**Available arguments** (type a space after the command, don't type the <>):
<**series name**>, <**page**>, <**@User, User ID or User tag**>, $mm serv <server ID>
Add **--** in front of a series, character, tag or note to exclude it from the search.
For multiple arguments, separate them with a **$**

__Example:__ *$mmwr Re:Zero*
__**SLASH COMMANDS** Example:__ */mm /wr Re:Zero*

7/17 - Tutorial
:do: **DISCOVER THE FATE YOU HAVE WITH ANOTHER PLAYER**
Use $fate @user


:do: **ASK A YES/NO QUESTION TO MUDAE**
Use $42ball <your question>


:do: **GET A RANDOM QUOTE**
Use $quotimage to get a random quote plus a random image.


:do: **BLOW UP SOMETHING**
Use $beam <anything>


:do: **TRY TO BEGIN A BLACK TEA GAME**
Use $blacktea to start a multiplayer turn-based word game.

{Embed}
8/17 - Tutorial
:do: **ADD A TEXT NOTE TO A CHARACTER YOU OWN**
Use $note <character> $ <text>
The text will be displayed in front of the character when you type $mm


:do: **SEARCH NOTED CHARACTERS WITH $FN**
Use $fn <text>
Notes are useful to search characters depending on how you noted them.


:do: **REMOVE A NOTE**
The syntax is: $note <character>$


:do: **SORT YOUR CHARACTERS**
Type $sm <character> to put a character at the 1st position of your harem, which means it is your favorite.


:do: **USE THE SEARCH COMMAND TO SEE MORE SORTING OPTIONS**
To find more sorting options, type $search sm


**Reward: 200:kakera:**

[05-Oct-22 06:37 PM] 09Miles#8861
$search sm


[05-Oct-22 06:37 PM] Mudae#0807
**$sortmarry**: ($sm) Sort your characters. *$sm Rem$Asuna*
**$sortmarrypos**: ($smp) Sort your characters by starting from a specific position. *$smp Asuna$Rem*
**$sortmarry$mm<flag>**: ($sm$mm<flag>) Sort your characters in the order displayed by the specified harem flag(s). *$sm$mmrg*
**$sortmarrynote**: ($smn) Sort your characters by their harem note. *$smn NFT$FT*
**$sortmarryseries**: ($smser) Sort your characters by their series. *$smser Re:Zero$SAO*
**$sortmarry abc**: Sort your characters by alphabetical order.
**$sortmarry reverse**: Sort your characters from the last position to the first position.
**$ssl**: Sort your Soulmate list.

{Embed}
9/17 - Tutorial
:do: **SEE A LIST OF ALIASES FOR A CHARACTER**
Use $al <character>
You can change the character name for an available alias with $alias <alias name>


:do: **ADD A CUSTOM SECONDARY ALIAS**
Use $a2 <character> $ <text>
When you roll or use $im for this character, your custom text will be displayed instead of the second alias.


:do: **TYPE $SELFRESET**
This will display all the commands you need to fully reset some parts of what you added.
The admin version of this command is $fullreset


:do: **LIKE A CHARACTER**
Type $like <character>
You can like any character, it will be added to your likelist and will participate to the global like ranks calculation.


:do: **CHECK YOUR LIST OF LIKED CHARACTERS**
Use $likelist


**Reward: 200:kakera:**

$al Lancer

[05-Oct-22 06:38 PM] 09Miles#8861
$selfreset


[05-Oct-22 06:38 PM] Mudae#0807
Syntaxes:
**$selfresetalias**: reset all aliases to the default value for ALL YOUR characters ($a)
**$selfresetalias2**: remove all the custom secondary aliases for ALL YOUR characters ($a2)
**$selfresetimg**: reset all images positions to the default value for ALL YOUR characters ($c)
**$selfresetcustimg**: remove all the custom images for ALL YOUR characters ($ai)
**$noteremoveall**: remove all harem notes for ALL YOUR characters ($n)
**$wishremoveall**: clean your $wishlist
**$enableall**: clean your $disablelist
**$antienableall**: clean your $antidisablelist
**$selfresetkeys**: clean all the keys for ALL YOUR characters (not soulkeys)
**$divorceall**: divorce ALL YOUR characters.

Spend your:kakera:to build the 12 floors of the tower:
- Choose a different perk each time you build a floor
- The next floor is more expensive (+5000 per floor, $towervalue)
- You can restart your tower and be refunded with $destroy
- The construction might be infinite: if you manage to build the 12 floors, you can build an additional tower with lower bonuses (the cost keeps increasing)


Your current level is **0** 
The next level costs **5000**:kakera:
You have **1914**:kakera:

Build a floor by using **$build <perk number>**

List of perks and their corresponding numbers:

**1** = +2 wishlist slots
**2** = Increased spawn chance for your $firstwish: **+**50%
**3** = +1 disablelist slot and +1627.8 disablelist size
**4** = 30% chance to earn a 2nd key when you get a bronze key on your wishes
**5** = 20% chance to earn a 2nd key when you get a silver key on your wishes
**6** = 10% chance to earn a 2nd key when you get a gold key on your wishes
**7** = Max kakera power increased to 110%
**8** = Kakera reactions cost -4% kakera power
**9** = Gold keys max bonus increased by +500 kakera/3h
**10** = Light kakera give +1 random kakera
**11** = +1 roll per hour
**12** = $colormm and $colorpr commands unlocked

4, 5 & 6 also give +1% chance for chaos keys and don't work for wished series

[05-Oct-22 06:40 PM] Mudae#0807
**$profilebadge**: ($pb) Change the badges/mudapins displayed on your profile.
**$bronze**: Upgrade your Bronze badge to get more wishlist slots. See `$kakera`
**$silver**: Upgrade your Silver badge to get more wishes. See `$kakera`
**$gold**: Upgrade your Gold badge to react more often on kakera. See `$kakera`
**$sapphire**: Upgrade your Sapphire badge to get more rolls. See `$kakera`
**$ruby**: Upgrade your Ruby badge to get miscellaneous rewards. See `$kakera`
**$emerald**: Upgrade your Emerald badge to get free claim resets. See `$kakera`
**$badgevalue**: (MOD) Change the cost of the kakera badges.
**$mudapin**: ($mp) Your mudapins. See `$infopin`
**$badges**: Your list of badges and mudapins.
**$profilearrange**: ($pa) Arrange the order of the categories on your profile.
**$kakerarefund**: (MOD) Refund the kakera badges of someone.
**$kakerarefundall**: (MOD) Refund kakera badges for everyone in your server.

12/17 - Tutorial
:do: **TRY TO BEGIN A GREEN TEA GAME**
Use $greentea to start another multiplayer word game.


:do: **USE $MYID**
This is a shortcut to get your user and server Discord IDs.
To get the ID of another user or server, you need to enable the developer mode in your Discord settings. Then:
- (PC) Right click on the user avatar or server icon.
- (Mobile) Tap on the user avatar or on the 3 dots for the server.


:do: **DISPLAY THE AVATAR OF SOMEONE ELSE WITH THEIR DISCORD ID**
Use $avatar <another user ID>
To get the user ID, see above.


:do: **DISPLAY THE CHARACTERS OF SOMEONE ELSE WITH THEIR DISCORD ID**
Use $mm <another user ID>
To get the user ID, see above. Because it's better to not mention someone!


**Reward: completion badge lvl I**

{Embed}
The Green Teaword will start!
‚Äã
To participate, **react** on ‚úÖ.


**Goal**: Be the fastest to write a word containing the group of 3 letters indicated.
You can't reuse a word already played.


Settings during this cooldown:
**$pts** <number> to redefine the number of points to reach (between 5 and 1000. Current: 30)
**$time** <number> to redefine the minimum response time, in seconds (between 3 and 50. Current: 10)
**$syll** <number> to redefine the number of possible groups of 3 letters (between 10 and 9000. Lowest values are easier. Current: 1400)


If you are a server mod, you can **set** these values for all the future games with **$greenteapts**, **$greenteatime**, **$teasyll**

You can stop the game for everyone with $exitgame

{Embed}
13/17 - Tutorial
:do: **DISABLE A SERIES TO GET BETTER ROLLS**
Use $disable <series>
The characters of a series you disabled won't appear when you roll.
This helps lowering the pool of available characters.
Wished characters are not disabled.


:do: **CHECK YOUR DISABLELIST**
Use $disablelist


:do: **SEARCH A BUNDLE WITH THE B FLAG**
A bundle has multiple series. For example, type $ima mobile games
To display the list of series in that bundle (instead of the characters), add the flag "b".
Example: $imab mobile games


:do: **DISABLE A BUNDLE**
Use $disable <bundle name>
You can also find the list of bundles a series belong to by typing $imab <series>


:do: **REMOVE 2 ENTRIES FROM YOUR DISABLELIST**
In one single command: use $enable <series or bundle> $ <series or bundle>
The separator for multiple characters or series is always a "$"


**Reward: +2 $preset for disablelist**

{Embed}
13/17 - Tutorial
:did: **DISABLE A SERIES TO GET BETTER ROLLS**
Use $disable <series>
The characters of a series you disabled won't appear when you roll.
This helps lowering the pool of available characters.
Wished characters are not disabled.


:did: **CHECK YOUR DISABLELIST**
Use $disablelist


:did: **SEARCH A BUNDLE WITH THE B FLAG**
A bundle has multiple series. For example, type $ima mobile games
To display the list of series in that bundle (instead of the characters), add the flag "b".
Example: $imab mobile games


:did: **DISABLE A BUNDLE**
Use $disable <bundle name>
You can also find the list of bundles a series belong to by typing $imab <series>


:do: **REMOVE 2 ENTRIES FROM YOUR DISABLELIST**
In one single command: use $enable <series or bundle> $ <series or bundle>
The separator for multiple characters or series is always a "$"


**Reward: +2 $preset for disablelist**


[05-Oct-22 06:45 PM] 09Miles#8861
$disablelist

{Embed}
14/17 - Tutorial
:do: **ANTIDISABLE A SERIES**
Use $ad <series>
When you antidisable a series, the series won't be disabled even if it's in your $disablelist
This is useful when you want to enable a specific series from a bundle you disabled.


:do: **REMOVE A SERIES FROM YOUR ANTIDISABLELIST**
Use $ae <series>


:do: **DISABLE OCCIDENTAL SERIES**
Use $togglewestern
This COMPLETELY disables the series from the "Western" bundle ($imab western), such as cartoons, comics...
Wished and antidisabled characters don't bypass this toggle.
This doesn't disable occidental video games.


:do: **ENABLE OCCIDENTAL SERIES**
It's a toggle: you just have to type $togglewestern again.
You can do the same for IRL people ($imab IRL) by using $toggleirl


:do: **RENAME YOUR CLAIM MESSAGE**
Use $rc to rename the message displayed when you claimed someone.


**Reward: +2 $preset for antidisablelist**


[05-Oct-22 06:46 PM] 09Miles#8861

You can already claim someone!
You have **1** $freeclaim
This command will reset your current claim timer (wasted if you don't claim anyone before the next claim reset)

‚ö† Recent servers don't have any $freeclaim and you can't get any besides special occasions such as the tutorial, events or long outages (with **$getfc**).
You won't be asked for a confirmation anymore after the first use of this command: type **$fcu** to check your number of $freeclaim left.


[05-Oct-22 06:48 PM] 09Miles#8861

[05-Oct-22 06:48 PM] Mudae#0807
Syntax: $renameclaim <Text that will replace your current claim message>
Insert the words `charname` to define the position of the character name and `username` to define the position of your username.

Example: $renameclaim üçí username and charname are now married! üçí
username and charname will be replaced in bold.
To replace all spaces by `_` (for <https://memegen.link/>), use `_username` and `_charname`
For the default message, use `$rc reset` (or `$rc reset @user` if you are a server moderator)

[05-Oct-22 06:49 PM] 09Miles#8861
$wishdm


[05-Oct-22 06:49 PM] Mudae#0807
Choose what should be private about your wishes.

Syntax: `$wishdm <get a DM when the character spawns (y/n)> <disable public ping when the character spawns (y/n)> <private wishlist (y/n)>`

Replace by **y** for yes or by **n** for no

Example (full private): **$wishdm y y y**
=> You get a DM when a character spawns
=> You don't get a public ping
=> Your wishlist is private

Current value: $wishdm n  n  n


[05-Oct-22 06:49 PM] 09Miles#8861
$wishdm y

[05-Oct-22 06:49 PM] 09Miles#8861
$rdmimg


[05-Oct-22 06:49 PM] Mudae#0807
Syntaxes:
**$randomimg 0**: (default value) Images appearing during __your__ rolls are not random.
**$randomimg 1**: Images are random for ALL your rolls.
**$randomimg 2**: Images are only random for your rolls of UNCLAIMED characters.
**$randomimg 3**: Images are only random for your rolls of CLAIMED characters.
**$randomimg 4**: Images are only random for your rolls of characters IN YOUR HAREM.
**$randomimg 5**: Images are random for all your rolls EXCEPT for the characters from your harem.

**$randomimg gif 1**: Gifs are never displayed when you roll.
**$randomimg gif 2**: INSTEAD of displaying a random image, a random gif is displayed if there is any.

**$randomimg cust 1**: Custom images are never displayed when you roll.
**$randomimg cust 2**: INSTEAD of displaying a random image, a custom image is displayed if there is any.
Default values: $randomimg gif 0 and $randomimg cust 0


[05-Oct-22 06:50 PM] 09Miles#8861
$rdmimg 0

{Embed}
16/17 - Tutorial
:do: **DEFINE YOUR FIRSTWISH**
Use $firstwish, certain perks give a spawn bonus to the character you chose as a $firstwish


:do: **INITIATE AND COMPLETE A CHARACTER TRADE WITH SOMEONE**
Type $trade and mention a user in your server ($trade @someone)
Then, type the name of a character you own.
If you just want to give a character, use $give


:do: **TYPE $SEARCH GIVE PAGE**
To know how to give pages of your harem.
The page numbers correspond to the characters displayed when you type $mm WITHOUT any flag.


:do: **DECLINE AN ATTEMPT TO DIVORCE 2 SPECIFIED CHARACTERS**
In one command. Use $divorce and deny the divorce at the last moment.
The separator for multiple characters or series is always a "$"


:do: **DEFINE THE PERSONALITY OF A CHARACTER YOU OWN**
Use $skills and follow the instructions.


**Reward: +50% spawn bonus for your $firstwish**

16/17 - Tutorial
:did: **DEFINE YOUR FIRSTWISH**
Use $firstwish, certain perks give a spawn bonus to the character you chose as a $firstwish


:do: **INITIATE AND COMPLETE A CHARACTER TRADE WITH SOMEONE**
Type $trade and mention a user in your server ($trade @someone)
Then, type the name of a character you own.
If you just want to give a character, use $give


:do: **TYPE $SEARCH GIVE PAGE**
To know how to give pages of your harem.
The page numbers correspond to the characters displayed when you type $mm WITHOUT any flag.


:do: **DECLINE AN ATTEMPT TO DIVORCE 2 SPECIFIED CHARACTERS**
In one command. Use $divorce and deny the divorce at the last moment.
The separator for multiple characters or series is always a "$"


:do: **DEFINE THE PERSONALITY OF A CHARACTER YOU OWN**
Use $skills and follow the instructions.


**Reward: +50% spawn bonus for your $firstwish**

$search


[05-Oct-22 06:56 PM] Mudae#0807
Syntax: $search **english keywords separated by a space**.
Examples:
*$s claim timer*
*$s harem flags*
*$s display kakera when rolling*
*$s divorce left user*
Remember that you can often get more infos just by typing the command.


[05-Oct-22 06:56 PM] 09Miles#8861
$s mm


[05-Oct-22 06:56 PM] Mudae#0807
**info flags**: Add those letters to some commands ($mm, $ima...) to display different informations:
**w** (waifu), **h** (husbando), **wh** (both genders), **w=** (waifu without both genders), **h=** (husbando without both genders)
**g** (game), **g-** (animanga), **gg-** (both), **g=** (game only), **g-=** (animanga only)
**a** (series list), **a+** (series names), **b** (series bundles), **p** (character search if you type some text), **s** (DM)

**r** (claim ranks), **r-** (claim ranks not sorted), **l** (like ranks), **l-** (like ranks not sorted),
**k** (kakera value), **k=** (kakera sorted), **k-** (kakera base value)
**y** (keys only), **y=** (keys sorted), **y+** (with full harem), **y-** (without keys)
Equivalent for soulkeys: **y!**, **y!=**, **y!+**, **y!-**
**c** (embedcolored), **c+** (with full harem), **c-** (without embedcolor)

**t** (type of rolls), **m** (main names), **d** (img/alias details), **v** (hide details such as notes), **n** (not noted), **n+** (noted only)
**u** (unclaimed), **o** (owner names), **o=** (owned only), **o-** (not owned by you), **o+** (owned by you)
**o!** (flags are about you when checking another user)
**x** (disabled), **x+** (with full harem), **x-** (not disabled)
**q!** (inexact search), **q=** (exact search), **q+** (exact start), **q-** (exact end), **==** (alphabetical sort)
**i** (images), **i-** (hide images if DM)

**Available arguments** (type a space after the command, don't type the <>):
<**series name**>, <**page**>, <**@User, User ID or User tag**>, $mm serv <server ID>
Add **--** in front of a series, character, tag or note to exclude it from the search.
For multiple arguments, separate them with a **$**

__Example:__ *$mmwr Re:Zero*
__**SLASH COMMANDS** Example:__ */mm /wr Re:Zero*

$skills


[05-Oct-22 06:57 PM] Mudae#0807
Define the personality of a character with the following syntax:
**$sk <Name of a character from your harem> <Yandere pts> <Tsundere pts> <Kuudere pts> <Dandere pts> <Deredere pts>**
Example: `$skills Rem 0 3 0 0 2`

Your arena level is **0** so the sum can't exceed **5** (limited to 5 max per skill)

Your character earns:
**+2**‚öî per Yandere point
**+1**‚öî **+1**üõ° per Tsundere point
**+2**üõ° per Kuudere point
**+1.5**üìî per Dandere point (rounded)
**+8%**üíó per Deredere point

‚öî: ATTACK pts, üõ°: DEFENSE pts, üìî: STUDY pts (for better loots), üíó: KOKORO pts (= Life pts)

This command isn't limited, you can change the personality of your character at will.
**You can fight other players or bots in a turn-based minigame called waifuarena. To start a game with $arena, you need the bot Mudae GM:**
<https://discordapp.com/oauth2/authorize?client_id=557949639555416084&permissions=537159744&scope=bot>
Mudae GM handles the following same commands by adding gm at the end: **$skillsgm**, $vsgm, $dsgm, $favarenagm

{Embed}
17/17 - Tutorial
:do: **CHECK YOUR KAKERA TOWER**
Type $kt
This is the command for infos and progression related to the kakera tower.


:do: **UPGRADE A TOWER LEVEL**
Use $build <floor number you want>


:do: **TRY TO DESTROY YOUR TOWER**
To get back the kakera you invested in the tower.


:do: [FINAL EXAM]
**FIND ALL THE __FEMALE__ CHARACTERS FROM THE SERIES "AOT" WHO HAVE "ANN" IN THEIR NAME**
In one single exact command. Remember how to get the subcommands of $ima and how to add flags.


:do: **TYPE $HELP**
This tutorial only covers a few commands. Type $help to get a DM with the full list of MAIN commands.


**Reward: 400:kakera:**


[05-Oct-22 06:58 PM] 09Miles#8861
$kt


[05-Oct-22 06:58 PM] Mudae#0807


{Embed}
Spend your:kakera:to build the 12 floors of the tower:
- Choose a different perk each time you build a floor
- The next floor is more expensive (+5000 per floor, $towervalue)
- You can restart your tower and be refunded with $destroy
- The construction might be infinite: if you manage to build the 12 floors, you can build an additional tower with lower bonuses (the cost keeps increasing)


Your current level is **0** 
The next level costs **5000**:kakera:
You have **1313**:kakera:

Build a floor by using **$build <perk number>**

List of perks and their corresponding numbers:

**1** = +2 wishlist slots
**2** = Increased spawn chance for your $firstwish: **+**50%
**3** = +1 disablelist slot and +1627.8 disablelist size
**4** = 30% chance to earn a 2nd key when you get a bronze key on your wishes
**5** = 20% chance to earn a 2nd key when you get a silver key on your wishes
**6** = 10% chance to earn a 2nd key when you get a gold key on your wishes
**7** = Max kakera power increased to 110%
**8** = Kakera reactions cost -4% kakera power
**9** = Gold keys max bonus increased by +500 kakera/3h
**10** = Light kakera give +1 random kakera
**11** = +1 roll per hour
**12** = $colormm and $colorpr commands unlocked

4, 5 & 6 also give +1% chance for chaos keys and don't work for wished series

{Embed}
How to collect kakera in your server (change the options with $togglekakera):
- $dailykakera
- React on the:kakera:that could appear on ** some already claimed** rolls ($setrare)
- Divorce a character with **$divorce** (value depends on claim/like ranks AND number of claimed characters)
- Trade with other players ($me with `<number> ka` or $givekakera)

You have **1313**:kakera:!

Melt your kakera into power badges:
:BronzeI:**Bronze I** ¬∑ Next level: **2000**:kakera: +1 wishlist slot
**Silver 0** ¬∑ Next level: **2000**:kakera: +25% wishlist spawn
**Gold 0** ¬∑ Next level: **3000**:kakera: -10% kakera power usage ($ku)
??? ¬∑ Prerequisites: Bronze I + Silver I + Gold I or 2 badges IV
??? ¬∑ Prerequisites: Bronze II + Silver II + Gold II or 2 badges IV
??? ¬∑ Prerequisites: Bronze III + Silver III + Gold III or 2 badges IV

**Kakeratower:** $kt
**Kakeraloots:** $infokl



Unlock a level with **$bronze**, **$silver**...
Get a special kakera **bonus** when you reach a level max (IV)!

Spend a total of **8000**:kakera:to enhance multitrading
Each level also gives you the corresponding **badge** on your $profile
Type **$kakerareward** to see the detailed rewards


[06-Oct-22 04:48 PM] 09Miles#8861
$tower


[06-Oct-22 04:48 PM] Mudae#0807


{Embed}
Spend your:kakera:to build the 12 floors of the tower:
- Choose a different perk each time you build a floor
- The next floor is more expensive (+5000 per floor, $towervalue)
- You can restart your tower and be refunded with $destroy
- The construction might be infinite: if you manage to build the 12 floors, you can build an additional tower with lower bonuses (the cost keeps increasing)


Your current level is **0** 
The next level costs **5000**:kakera:
You have **1313**:kakera:

Build a floor by using **$build <perk number>**

List of perks and their corresponding numbers:

**1** = +2 wishlist slots
**2** = Increased spawn chance for your $firstwish: **+**50%
**3** = +1 disablelist slot and +1627.8 disablelist size
**4** = 30% chance to earn a 2nd key when you get a bronze key on your wishes
**5** = 20% chance to earn a 2nd key when you get a silver key on your wishes
**6** = 10% chance to earn a 2nd key when you get a gold key on your wishes
**7** = Max kakera power increased to 110%
**8** = Kakera reactions cost -4% kakera power
**9** = Gold keys max bonus increased by +500 kakera/3h
**10** = Light kakera give +1 random kakera
**11** = +1 roll per hour
**12** = $colormm and $colorpr commands unlocked

4, 5 & 6 also give +1% chance for chaos keys and don't work for wished series

How to collect kakera in your server (change the options with $togglekakera):
- $dailykakera
- React on the:kakera:that could appear on ** some already claimed** rolls ($setrare)
- Divorce a character with **$divorce** (value depends on claim/like ranks AND number of claimed characters)
- Trade with other players ($me with `<number> ka` or $givekakera)

You have **1313**:kakera:!

Melt your kakera into power badges:
:BronzeI:**Bronze I** ¬∑ Next level: **2000**:kakera: +1 wishlist slot
**Silver 0** ¬∑ Next level: **2000**:kakera: +25% wishlist spawn
**Gold 0** ¬∑ Next level: **3000**:kakera: -10% kakera power usage ($ku)
??? ¬∑ Prerequisites: Bronze I + Silver I + Gold I or 2 badges IV
??? ¬∑ Prerequisites: Bronze II + Silver II + Gold II or 2 badges IV
??? ¬∑ Prerequisites: Bronze III + Silver III + Gold III or 2 badges IV

**Kakeratower:** $kt
**Kakeraloots:** $infokl



Unlock a level with **$bronze**, **$silver**...
Get a special kakera **bonus** when you reach a level max (IV)!

Spend a total of **8000**:kakera:to enhance multitrading
Each level also gives you the corresponding **badge** on your $profile
Type **$kakerareward** to see the detailed rewards

[07-Oct-22 04:16 PM] 09Miles#8861
$togglesnipe


[07-Oct-22 04:16 PM] Mudae#0807
Use one of the syntaxes below to change the way people can snipe characters on your server (= if players are able to claim the characters rolled by other players or not). Wishseries aren't considered as wishes for this command.

**$togglesnipe 0**: (default value, no restriction) Any character rolled can be sniped by anyone.

**$togglesnipe 1**: (partial restriction) When someone rolls a character they have in their character wishlist, this character can't be sniped for 8 seconds.

**$togglesnipe 2**: (full restriction) Any character rolled can't be sniped for 8 seconds.

**$togglesnipe 3**: (wish restriction 1) When someone rolls a WISHED character, this character can't be sniped for 8 seconds EXCEPT for people wishing for this character (AND the roller)

**$togglesnipe 4**: (wish restriction 2) When someone rolls a WISHED character, this character can't be sniped for 8 seconds EXCEPT for people wishing for this character (the roller CAN'T claim this character either, except if they wished for it)

**$togglesnipe 5**: (combined restriction 1) Any character rolled can't be sniped for 8 second(s) EXCEPT for people wishing for this character (AND the roller)

**$togglesnipe 6**: (combined restriction 2) Any character rolled can't be sniped for 8 second(s) EXCEPT for people wishing for this character (the roller CAN'T claim this wish except if they wished for it)

You can add an option to modify the 8 seconds default value.
Example: **$togglesnipe 1 2.5**
=> Anyone will be able to react after 2.5 seconds.

Current value: **0**

[07-Oct-22 04:17 PM] 09Miles#8861
$keys


[07-Oct-22 04:17 PM] Mudae#0807
Unlock the full capacities of your waifu/husbando!
Each time you roll a character owned by yourself, the **key level** of this character is increased by 1.

__Rewards:__
(All of the following rewards are bound to the character reaching the corresponding key level and are not reset if you divorce or trade the character)

LVL 1 (Bronze) => **$embedcolor** command unlocked to customize the embed color.
LVL 2 => +10% kakera value.
LVL 3 (Silver) => Teal and green kakera spawning on this character are replaced by **orange kakera**.
LVL 4 => +10% kakera value.
LVL 5 => +10% kakera value.
LVL 6 (Gold) => When you roll this character, you earn its **kakera value** (4500 max/3h, $bku)
LVL 7 => +10% kakera value.
LVL 8 => +10% kakera value.
LVL 9 => +10% kakera value.
LVL 10 (Chaos) => Kakera reactions on this character cost **half the power** for the character owner.
LVL 11 and above: +5% kakera value.

If you rolled a character 10 times by yourself, the character enters your **SOULMATE LIST**.
Check how many times you rolled your characters with $mmy! (called soulkeys)

Your Soulmate list ($sl) is a global list you can access to any server, it also works as a backup you can copy to new servers with some restrictions ($soulcopy).
Soulmates are not erased if you trade or divorce them on the original server (nor with the key reset commands).

__Additional commands:__
Filter for keys: **y** ($mmy, $imay...) and more (see $s flags)
Ladders: **$tsy** (character), **$tsyb** (best character/player), **$tsyt** (total keys)
Soulmate list commands: see $s soulmate
Disable server keys system with $togglekeys

Notes: wishing a claimed character still enables it, and the spawn is boosted by Silver/Ruby. Orange kakera perk affects $mk but you can't earn a key with $mk
Characters traded or gifted are not affected by the key leveling/kakera perk for 3 hours after the trade/gift.

The Green Teaword will start!
‚Äã
To participate, **react** on ‚úÖ.


**Goal**: Be the fastest to write a word containing the group of 3 letters indicated.

Settings during this cooldown:

**$time** <number> to redefine the minimum response time, in seconds (between 3 and 50. Current: 10)
**$syll** <number> to redefine the number of possible groups of 3 letters (between 10 and 9000. Lowest values are easier. Current: 1400)


If you are a server mod, you can **set** these values for all the future games with **$greenteapts**, **$greenteatime**, **$teasyll**

You can stop the game for everyone with $exitgame

[07-Oct-22 04:21 PM] Mudae#0807
Syntax: **$tuarrange <category> <category> ...**
Effect: arrange the order of the categories for your **$tu** command.
Categories not specified in the command will be hidden.

List of categories:
**claim, rolls, daily, keys, kakerareact, kakerapower, kakerainfo, kakerastock, rt, dk, pokemon, vote, rollsreset, jump**
*jump* is used to jump a line (up to 10 jump)

Example (default value): $ta claim rolls daily jump kakerareact kakerapower kakerainfo kakerastock jump rt dk vote

{Embed}
How to collect kakera in your server (change the options with $togglekakera):
- $dailykakera
- React on the:kakera:that could appear on ** some already claimed** rolls ($setrare)
- Divorce a character with **$divorce** (value depends on claim/like ranks AND number of claimed characters)
- Trade with other players ($me with `<number> ka` or $givekakera)

You have **1611**:kakera:!

Melt your kakera into power badges:
:BronzeI:**Bronze I** ¬∑ Next level: **2000**:kakera: +1 wishlist slot
**Silver 0** ¬∑ Next level: **2000**:kakera: +25% wishlist spawn
**Gold 0** ¬∑ Next level: **3000**:kakera: -10% kakera power usage ($ku)
??? ¬∑ Prerequisites: Bronze I + Silver I + Gold I or 2 badges IV
??? ¬∑ Prerequisites: Bronze II + Silver II + Gold II or 2 badges IV
??? ¬∑ Prerequisites: Bronze III + Silver III + Gold III or 2 badges IV

**Kakeratower:** $kt
**Kakeraloots:** $infokl



Unlock a level with **$bronze**, **$silver**...
Get a special kakera **bonus** when you reach a level max (IV)!

Spend a total of **8000**:kakera:to enhance multitrading
Each level also gives you the corresponding **badge** on your $profile
Type **$kakerareward** to see the detailed rewards


[07-Oct-22 10:20 PM] 09Miles#8861
$tower


[07-Oct-22 10:20 PM] Mudae#0807


{Embed}
Spend your:kakera:to build the 12 floors of the tower:
- Choose a different perk each time you build a floor
- The next floor is more expensive (+5000 per floor, $towervalue)
- You can restart your tower and be refunded with $destroy
- The construction might be infinite: if you manage to build the 12 floors, you can build an additional tower with lower bonuses (the cost keeps increasing)


Your current level is **0** 
The next level costs **5000**:kakera:
You have **1611**:kakera:

Build a floor by using **$build <perk number>**

List of perks and their corresponding numbers:

**1** = +2 wishlist slots
**2** = Increased spawn chance for your $firstwish: **+**50%
**3** = +1 disablelist slot and +1627.8 disablelist size
**4** = 30% chance to earn a 2nd key when you get a bronze key on your wishes
**5** = 20% chance to earn a 2nd key when you get a silver key on your wishes
**6** = 10% chance to earn a 2nd key when you get a gold key on your wishes
**7** = Max kakera power increased to 110%
**8** = Kakera reactions cost -4% kakera power
**9** = Gold keys max bonus increased by +500 kakera/3h
**10** = Light kakera give +1 random kakera
**11** = +1 roll per hour
**12** = $colormm and $colorpr commands unlocked

4, 5 & 6 also give +1% chance for chaos keys and don't work for wished series

Hi there! **Youtube isn't supported anymore**. Youtube support has been removed because youtube is forcing discord to unverify bots which stream audio from it. Possible solutions:

- Try the following platforms: BandCamp, Vimeo, Soundcloud, Twitch for direct track links.
- You can search for the song instead and we'll try to find the best version using our other providers.
- To overcome with this problem we have decided to add **support for playlists in FredBoat** where you will be able to create your own playlists. The feature will be live soon. Keep checking the FredBoat community server for the latest updates.

Multiplayer help
d!play
Start a multiplayer game
(2+ people required, one game per server)
d!pass
Skip a turn
d!die
Drop out of a game
(works only on your turn)
You can use d!helpdict and d!helpaddons to change the style of the game
